1.0	The (>): This “>” means output text into a file.
Usage:
Echo “How are you?” > greetings.txt

2.0	The (>>): This means append texts to a file.
Usage:
Echo “Today is a good day” >> greetins.txt

3.0	Pipes: The primary purpose of the pipe command is to connect the output of command directly into the input of another (|)
Usage:
whoami | sort
The above command will display the name of the system user

whoami | wc -w
The above command will display the word count of the w which in this case is 0.
